Accordingly Charles von Miltitz (?1490—†1529)‚ by birth a Saxon nobleman, and now both papal chamberlain and agent at Rome for the Saxon Courts‚ was appointed Nuncio 15 Oct. 1518 (Loescher, ii. 554), and sent to bring him the Golden Rose. Miltitz left ltaly Nov. 1518; and, after interviews with Spalatin and the Elector in December which led him to see the necessity of disavowing Tetzel († 4 July 1519), disgraced that worthy at Leipzig, and then went on to ARenburg, where he had 3 friendly meeting with Luther in Spalatin's house 6 Jan. 1519. In letters of Jan. 1519 Luther gives [No. 21] an account to the Elector of his agreement with Miltitz (de Wette, i. 208 sq.; tr.
